Currently there is an encoding issues when importing issues in JPO. It is somehow related to https://ecosystem.atlassian.net/browse/AO-386

As explained by one of JIRA Portfolio developer:
{quote}
Due to a bug in ActiveObjects (see link above)  some columns in our JPO tables are defined as VARCHAR instead of NVARCHAR, which causes the problem in MSSQL server for characters other than LATIN_1
{quote}

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Portfolio Server*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOCLOUD-425].
  {panel}

Currently there is an encoding issues when importing issues in JPO. It is somehow related to https://ecosystem.atlassian.net/browse/AO-386

As explained by one of JIRA Portfolio developer:
{quote}
we do have a bug in the DDL - the JPO tables are using VARCHAR instead of NVARCHAR columns, which causes the problem in MSSQL server for characters other than LATING_1 , LATIN_1
{quote}

